def plot_deviance(model, X, y):
    X_training, X_testing, y_training, y_testing = train_test_split(X, y)
    print(X_training.shape, y_training.shape)
    model.fit(X_training, y_training)
    X_training.info()
    test_scores = np.zeros((params['n_estimators'],), dtype=np.float64)

    for i, y_pred in enumerate(model.staged_predict(X_testing)):
        test_scores[i] = mean_squared_error(y_testing, y_pred)

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))
    plt.subplot(1, 1, 1)
    plt.plot(
    np.arange(params["n_estimators"]) + 1,
    model.train_score_,
    "b-",
    label="Training Set Deviance",
    )
    plt.plot(
    np.arange(params['n_estimators']) + 1,
    test_scores,
    "r-",
    label="Test Set Deviance")
    
plot_deviance(model, X, y)

In [15]:
def plot_feature_importance(model, X, y, n_first=1):
    X_training, X_testing, y_training, y_testing = train_test_split(X, y)
    model.fit(X_training, y_training)
    feature_importance = model.feature_importances_
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(30, 10 + n_first/12))
    
    result = permutation_importance(
    model, X_testing, y_testing, n_repeats = 30, random_state=13, n_jobs=-1)
    n = len(X_training.columns)
    sorted_idx = result.importances_mean.argsort()
   
    print(np.array(X_training.columns)[sorted_idx][::-1][:n_first])
    plt.boxplot(
    result.importances[sorted_idx][:n_first].T,
    vert=False,
    labels = np.array(X_training.columns)[sorted_idx][:n_first])
    plt.axvline(x=0.0, linestyle='dashed')
